obo:ECO_0006042  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4809  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: biochemical fractions of mouse forebrain show C9orf72 to be localized to both the pre- and post-synaptic compartment.\n\nFigure 2: IP+WB of PSD95 (DLG4) yields C9orf72 and Rab39b (Fig. 2a). Immunofluorescent imaging from C9-WT mossy fiber synapses demonstrated partial overlap of C9orf72 with pre-synaptic (Synpr), post-synaptic (PSD-95), and dendritic (MAP 2) proteins (Fig. 2c). C9orf72 was partially co-localized with Rab39b in the mossy fiber synapse region of C9-WT mice (Fig. 2c), indicating that C9orf72 shares synaptic localization with previously identified interactors.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Knockout C9orf72 mice were obtained through a generous gift from\"\n\nantibody:\nC9orf72, GeneTex, GTX634482, Ms monoclonal" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4809" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

